                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="arabiannights_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">the name often given to the <span class="ebi">Thousand and One Nights</span>, a collection of traditional stories from the Middle East, written in Arabic. Scheherezade marries a king who kills his wives after their first night together. She survives by telling him a different story every night. Many popular films, songs and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/pantomime#pantomime_sng_1" title="pantomimes definition"><span class="ndv">pantomimes</span></a> are based on some of these stories, such as <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/aladdin" title="Aladdin definition"><span class="ndv">Aladdin</span></a> and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sinbad-the-sailor" title="Sinbad the Sailor definition"><span class="ndv">Sinbad the Sailor</span></a></span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
